name: Choise
description: Ð¡hoice, a monk in the center of co-brothers ponders on a match. The plot refers to the ritual self-immolation and the protest between life and an endless series of reincarnations. In a more passive form, the author develops a notion of madness-or, if one chooses the term wisely, this is not despair; it is just despair on an infinite scale. In any case, it is something that may upset the balance of the circle of life.
